21/05/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The United Kingdom's defence ministry has signed a capacity-building agreement with the new Kosovo Security Force (KSF), media reported on Thursday (May 21st).
Under the accord, British experts will provide training to KSF members in different fields according to NATO standards.
"We hope that after signing this agreement and expanding our co-operation, Kosovo will manage to become a NATO member," British Ambassador to Kosovo Andrew Sparks said on Wednesday.
(Kosova Sot, Lajm, Info Press, Koha Ditore - 21/05/09)
